XXVIII. “At length, one of the most learned amongst them asked me about the Nile, its source, the special characteristics by which it rs distinguished from other rivers, and why it is that it is the only river that overflows in summer. I told them what l knew on the subject, what 1 had gethered from the sacred books which the priests alone may read and consult. 1 told them that it rises in the mountains of Aethiopia, on the furthest confines of Libya, where the east ends and the south begins.
